1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Linux?

Simple Definition

Linux is an operating system.

More precisely:

Linux = Linux Kernel + Tools + Software ‚Üí Forms a full OS.

‚∏ª

Plain English

Linux is software that lets you use hardware:
	‚Ä¢	CPU
	‚Ä¢	RAM
	‚Ä¢	Storage
	‚Ä¢	Network ports

Without OS ‚Üí hardware useless.

‚∏ª

Real-Life Analogy üè¢

Component	Computer
Building	Hardware
Manager	Linux
Workers	Apps

Linux manages resources.

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ Linux = Kernel + User Space

Linux OS has 2 main parts:

User Space ‚Üí Apps, tools, shells
Kernel Space ‚Üí Core OS engine

Kernel controls hardware, user space provides usability.

‚∏ª

